üìë Disk Management Commands
Command	            Description	                      Example

Get-Volume	        List volumes	                    Get-Volume
Get-Disk	          List physical disks	              Get-Disk
Initialize-Disk	    Initialize a new disk	            Initialize-Disk -Number 2
New-Partition	      Create a partition	              New-Partition -DiskNumber 2 -UseMaximumSize -AssignDriveLetter
Format-Volume	      Format partition	                Format-Volume -DriveLetter E -FileSystem NTFS

üì° Networking Commands
Command	            Description	            Example

Test-Connection	    Ping test	              Test-Connection google.com
Get-NetIPAddress	  Show IP addresses	      Get-NetIPAddress
Get-NetRoute	      Show routing table	    Get-NetRoute
Resolve-DnsName	    DNS lookup	            Resolve-DnsName microsoft.com

‚öôÔ∏è Process & Service Management Commands
Command	            Description	                    Example

Get-Process	        List running processes	        Get-Process
Stop-Process	      Stop a process by name or ID	  Stop-Process -Name notepad
Start-Process	      Launch a program	              Start-Process notepad
Get-Service	        List services	                  Get-Service
Start-Service	      Start a service	                Start-Service Spooler
Stop-Service	      Stop a service	                Stop-Service Spooler

üë§ User & System Info Commands
Command	            Description	              Example

Get-LocalUser	      List local users	        Get-LocalUser
Get-LocalGroup	    List local groups	        Get-LocalGroup
Get-EventLog	      View system logs	        Get-EventLog -LogName System -Newest 5

üñ®Ô∏è Printing Commands
Command	            Description	                    Example

Get-Printer	        List installed printers	        Get-Printer
Get-PrintJob	      View current print jobs	        Get-PrintJob
Remove-PrintJob	    Cancel a print job	            Remove-PrintJob -PrinterName 'HP' -ID 3

üìú Scripting Utilities
Command	            Description	                Example

Write-Output	      Display text	              Write-Output 'Hello World'
Write-Host	        Print text to console	      Write-Host 'Hello'
Read-Host	          Prompt user input	          $name = Read-Host 'Enter your name'
Start-Sleep	        Pause script	              Start-Sleep -Seconds 5
ForEach-Object	    Loop through items	        `Get-Process
